The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Orchid Chemicals has entered into a $100-million research collaboration and licensing agreement with Merck amp; Co for the discovery, development and commercialisation of agents for the treatment of bacterial and fungal infections. Orchid will be paid an undisclosed upfront sum, and is eligible to receive payments worth more than $100 million.                            
	 Alcatel-Lucent has signed a seven-year agreement with Club Med. Under the deal, Alcatel-Lucent and its global business partners will install and manage the companys hospitality solution.                            
	 Samsung Mobile has launched Omnia featuring a 3.2-inch LCD screen, auto-focus, face detection, auto-panorama shot and 32 GB and 24-GB memory.                            
	 TIL has inked a pact with Hyster for selling the latters lift trucks range in India, Nepal and Bhutan                            
	 Coca-Cola India has launched Sprite Xpress, a 350-ml pack, priced at Rs 15.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
